---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="DRpedia — What Is DRpedia? | MDRPedia"
    description="DRpedia is the colloquial name for MDRPedia in Eastern medical communities. Learn about the world's leading physician encyclopedia, also known as DRpedia in the Middle East, Asia, and Africa."
>
    <article class="disambig-page">
        <div class="container">
            <!-- Breadcrumb -->
            <nav class="disambig-breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
                <a href="/">MDRPedia</a> <span>/</span>
                <a href="/about">About</a> <span>/</span>
                <span aria-current="page">DRpedia</span>
            </nav>

            <!-- Hero -->
            <header class="disambig-hero">
                <span class="disambig-badge">Disambiguation</span>
                <h1>DRpedia</h1>
                <p class="disambig-subtitle">
                    The Eastern colloquial name for <strong>MDRPedia</strong> — The Physicians' Register.
                </p>
            </header>

            <!-- Infobox -->
            <aside class="disambig-infobox">
                <h4>At a Glance</h4>
                <dl>
                    <dt>Official Name</dt>
                    <dd><a href="/">MDRPedia</a></dd>
                    <dt>Colloquial Name</dt>
                    <dd>DRpedia</dd>
                    <dt>Used In</dt>
                    <dd>Middle East, South Asia, East Asia, Africa</dd>
                    <dt>Origin</dt>
                    <dd>"Dr." (universal honorific) + "pedia" (encyclopedia)</dd>
                    <dt>Western Equivalent</dt>
                    <dd><a href="/about/mdpedia">MDpedia</a></dd>
                    <dt>Website</dt>
                    <dd><a href="/">mdrpedia.com</a></dd>
                </dl>
            </aside>

            <!-- Main Content -->
            <section class="disambig-content">
                <h2>What is DRpedia?</h2>
                <p>
                    <strong>DRpedia</strong> is the informal name by which <a href="/">MDRPedia</a> is widely known
                    in Eastern medical communities. The name derives from <strong>Dr.</strong> (Doctor),
                    the universal honorific used across the Middle East, South Asia, East Asia, and Africa,
                    combined with <strong>-pedia</strong> (from "encyclopedia").
                </p>
                <p>
                    While the official platform name is MDRPedia, physicians, medical institutions, and
                    healthcare media across Eastern regions frequently use "DRpedia" as shorthand when
                    referencing the register in hospitals, medical conferences, and regional publications.
                </p>

                <h2>Why "Dr." in the East?</h2>
                <p>
                    In Eastern medical traditions, the <strong>Dr.</strong> prefix carries deep cultural significance.
                    Across countries including India, Pakistan, Egypt, Saudi Arabia, the UAE, China, Japan,
                    Nigeria, Kenya, and South Africa, physicians are universally addressed as "Doctor" rather
                    than by their degree acronym. The honorific transcends specific qualifications — whether
                    MBBS, MBChB, or MD — making "DRpedia" a natural and culturally resonant shorthand.
                </p>
                <p>
                    In many of these regions, the "Dr." title carries a weight of social respect and community
                    trust that extends beyond clinical practice. A physician is a Doctor first — a healer
                    known to patients, families, and communities by that single, powerful title.
                </p>

                <h2>DRpedia and MDpedia: Same Register</h2>
                <p>
                    It is important to note that DRpedia and <a href="/about/mdpedia">MDpedia</a> refer to
                    the same platform: <strong>MDRPedia</strong>. In Western medical communities — the Americas,
                    Europe, and Australasia — the platform is known as MDpedia, using the "MD" credential prefix.
                    Both names are recognized and direct to the same verified physician database.
                </p>

                <h2>Physicians from the East on MDRPedia</h2>
                <p>
                    MDRPedia's register includes thousands of verified physicians from Eastern regions,
                    covering landmark figures in medicine:
                </p>
                <ul class="region-list">
                    <li><strong>Middle East:</strong> Pioneers in cardiac surgery, ophthalmology, and humanitarian medicine</li>
                    <li><strong>South Asia:</strong> Leaders in tropical medicine, immunology, and public health</li>
                    <li><strong>East Asia:</strong> Innovators in traditional medicine integration, robotics, and genomics</li>
                    <li><strong>Africa:</strong> Champions of infectious disease control, maternal health, and community medicine</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>What MDRPedia Offers</h2>
                <ul class="feature-list">
                    <li><a href="/doctors">Verified physician profiles</a> across 85+ countries</li>
                    <li><a href="/rankings">Impact-based rankings</a> using the proprietary MDR Score</li>
                    <li><a href="/specialty">Specialty directories</a> covering every medical discipline</li>
                    <li><a href="/institutions">Institutional profiles</a> for hospitals and research centers</li>
                    <li><a href="/ethical-doctors">Ethics verification</a> with a transparent seal system</li>
                    <li><a href="/clinical-trials">Clinical trial tracking</a> linked to physician profiles</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>How to Access</h2>
                <p>
                    Whether you search for "DRpedia," "MDRPedia," or "MDpedia," you will find the same register
                    at <a href="/">mdrpedia.com</a>. The platform is free, open-access, and licensed under
                    Creative Commons (CC BY-SA 4.0).
                </p>
            </section>

            <!-- Related Links -->
            <nav class="disambig-related">
                <h3>Related Pages</h3>
                <div class="related-grid">
                    <a href="/about/mdpedia" class="related-card">
                        <span class="related-label">Western Name</span>
                        <strong>MDpedia</strong>
                        <p>The colloquial name used in the Americas, Europe, and Australasia</p>
                    </a>
                    <a href="/about" class="related-card">
                        <span class="related-label">About</span>
                        <strong>About MDRPedia</strong>
                        <p>Our methodology, history, and the Impact Quotient system</p>
                    </a>
                    <a href="/brand" class="related-card">
                        <span class="related-label">Design</span>
                        <strong>Brand System</strong>
                        <p>Logo, typography, tier seals, and editorial principles</p>
                    </a>
                    <a href="/doctors" class="related-card">
                        <span class="related-label">Register</span>
                        <strong>Browse Profiles</strong>
                        <p>Search the verified register of physicians worldwide</p>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </nav>
        </div>
    </article>

    <!-- FAQ Schema for SEO -->
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "FAQPage",
        "mainEntity": [
            {
                "@type": "Question",
                "name": "What is DRpedia?",
                "acceptedAnswer": {
                    "@type": "Answer",
                    "text": "DRpedia is the colloquial name for MDRPedia, the world's first independently-verified encyclopedia of physicians. The name is widely used in Eastern medical communities across the Middle East, South Asia, East Asia, and Africa."
                }
            },
            {
                "@type": "Question",
                "name": "Is DRpedia the same as MDpedia?",
                "acceptedAnswer": {
                    "@type": "Answer",
                    "text": "Yes. DRpedia and MDpedia both refer to MDRPedia (mdrpedia.com). DRpedia is the Eastern name (from 'Dr.'), while MDpedia is used in Western medical communities (from 'MD')."
                }
            },
            {
                "@type": "Question",
                "name": "Is DRpedia the same as MDRPedia?",
                "acceptedAnswer": {
                    "@type": "Answer",
                    "text": "Yes. DRpedia is the informal Eastern name for MDRPedia — The Physicians' Register. The official platform is MDRPedia at mdrpedia.com."
                }
            },
            {
                "@type": "Question",
                "name": "Why is it called DRpedia?",
                "acceptedAnswer": {
                    "@type": "Answer",
                    "text": "The name DRpedia comes from 'Dr.' (Doctor), the universal medical honorific used across the Middle East, South Asia, East Asia, and Africa, combined with '-pedia' (encyclopedia). Eastern physicians naturally shortened MDRPedia to DRpedia."
                }
            }
        ]
    })} />

    <!-- BreadcrumbList Schema -->
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
        "itemListElement": [
            { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "MDRPedia", "item": "https://mdrpedia.com" },
            { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "About", "item": "https://mdrpedia.com/about" },
            { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "DRpedia", "item": "https://mdrpedia.com/about/drpedia" }
        ]
    })} />
</Layout>

<style>
    .disambig-page { max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 20px 100px; }

    .disambig-breadcrumb {
        padding: 20px 0; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px;
        color: var(--ink-3); letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }
    .disambig-breadcrumb a { color: var(--ink-2); text-decoration: none; }
    .disambig-breadcrumb a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    .disambig-breadcrumb span { margin: 0 6px; }

    .disambig-badge {
        display: inline-block; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px;
        letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-blue);
        border: 1px solid var(--ink-blue); padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: var(--r-2);
        margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    .disambig-hero { padding: 40px 0 32px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); }
    .disambig-hero h1 {
        font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 3.2rem; font-weight: 400;
        color: var(--ink); margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    .disambig-subtitle { font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--ink-2); max-width: 50ch; }

    .disambig-infobox {
        float: right; width: 260px; margin: 32px 0 24px 32px;
        background: var(--paper-2); border: 1px solid var(--rule);
        border-radius: var(--r-3); padding: 20px;
    }
    .disambig-infobox h4 {
        font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.14em;
        text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-3); margin-bottom: 16px;
        padding-bottom: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    }
    .disambig-infobox dl { display: grid; gap: 8px; }
    .disambig-infobox dt {
        font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-3);
    }
    .disambig-infobox dd {
        font-size: 14px; color: var(--ink); margin: 0 0 8px;
        padding-bottom: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    }
    .disambig-infobox dd:last-child { border-bottom: none; padding-bottom: 0; margin-bottom: 0; }
    .disambig-infobox a { color: var(--ink-blue); text-decoration: underline; }

    .disambig-content { padding-top: 32px; }
    .disambig-content h2 {
        font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 400;
        color: var(--ink); margin: 2rem 0 0.8rem; padding-top: 1rem;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    }
    .disambig-content h2:first-child { border-top: none; margin-top: 0; padding-top: 0; }
    .disambig-content p { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--ink-2); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .disambig-content a { color: var(--ink-blue); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }

    .region-list {
        list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 1rem 0;
    }
    .region-list li {
        padding: 12px 16px; border-left: 3px solid var(--ink-blue);
        margin-bottom: 8px; background: var(--paper-2);
        font-size: 14px; color: var(--ink-2); line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .region-list li strong { color: var(--ink); }

    .feature-list {
        list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 1rem 0;
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 8px;
    }
    .feature-list li {
        padding: 10px 14px; background: var(--paper-2); border: 1px solid var(--rule);
        border-radius: var(--r-2); font-size: 14px;
    }
    .feature-list li a { color: var(--ink-blue); text-decoration: none; }
    .feature-list li a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    .disambig-related {
        margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 2px solid var(--rule);
        clear: both;
    }
    .disambig-related h3 {
        font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.18em;
        text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-3); margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .related-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
    .related-card {
        padding: 20px; background: var(--paper-2); border: 1px solid var(--rule);
        border-radius: var(--r-3); text-decoration: none; color: var(--ink);
        transition: border-color var(--t-fast) var(--ease);
    }
    .related-card:hover { border-color: var(--ink-blue); }
    .related-label {
        display: block; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px;
        letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-3);
        margin-bottom: 4px;
    }
    .related-card strong { font-size: 15px; display: block; margin-bottom: 4px; }
    .related-card p { font-size: 12px; color: var(--ink-3); margin: 0; }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .disambig-hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; }
        .disambig-infobox { float: none; width: 100%; margin: 24px 0; }
        .feature-list { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
        .related-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
</style>
